(24, 'A Beginner Guide to Forex Trading', 16, 29, '<p><b><font face=\"Arial\">A Beginner Guide to Forex Trading</font></b></p><p><b><font face=\"Arial\">What is Forex trading and how does it wrk in South Africa?</font></b></p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Web capture_21-2-2023_91943_www.bing.com.jpeg\" style=\"width: 100%;\"><b><font face=\"Arial\"><br></font></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\">Forex trading refers to the buying and selling of different\r\ncurrencies with the intention of making a profit. It is a decentralized global\r\nmarket that operates 24 hours a day, five days a week, with the largest trading\r\ncenters located in London, New York, and Tokyo.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\"><b>How Forex Trading Works</b><o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\">Forex trading operates on a simple concept - buy low and\r\nsell high. Forex traders buy currencies when the exchange rate is low and sell\r\nthem when the exchange rate is high. The exchange rate between two currencies\r\nis determined by the supply and demand of the currencies. When the demand for a\r\ncurrency is high, its value increases, and when the demand is low, its value\r\ndecreases.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\">Forex traders take advantage of these fluctuations in\r\nexchange rates to make a profit. For example, if the value of the South African\r\nRand (ZAR) decreases against the US Dollar (USD), a South African Forex trader\r\ncan buy USD using ZAR. When the value of the ZAR increases against the USD, the\r\ntrader can sell the USD and make a profit.<o:p></o:p></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\"><b>Trading Platforms</b></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Arial\"><b>binary options</b></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Web capture_21-2-2023_92320_www.bing.com.jpeg\" style=\"width: 50%;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><b><br></b></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">IQ Option is an online trading platform that allows users to\r\ntrade a variety of financial instruments, including stocks, forex,\r\ncryptocurrencies, and options. It was founded in 2013 and has grown in\r\npopularity due to its user-friendly interface and low minimum deposit\r\nrequirements.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the unique features of IQ Option is its proprietary\r\ntrading platform, which is designed to be simple and intuitive for beginners,\r\nwhile also offering advanced trading tools for more experienced traders. The\r\nplatform can be accessed through a web browser or a mobile app, and it offers a\r\nrange of analytical tools, including technical indicators and charting options.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Another key feature of IQ Option is its low minimum deposit\r\nrequirement, which makes it accessible to a wide range of traders. In addition,\r\nit offers competitive spreads and low trading fees, making it an attractive\r\nchoice for those who are looking to trade on a budget.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">One of the most popular instruments on the IQ Option\r\nplatform is options trading, which allows traders to speculate on the price\r\nmovements of underlying assets without actually owning them. IQ Option offers a\r\nvariety of options types, including binary options, digital options, and FX\r\noptions, each with different payout structures and expiry times.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><font face=\"Hind Madurai, sans-serif\"><b>Trading view</b></font><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"Web capture_21-2-2023_174025_www.bing.com.jpeg\" style=\"width: 50%;\"><font face=\"Hind Madurai, sans-serif\"><b><br></b></font></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">TradingView is a cloud-based charting and social networking\r\nplatform that is widely used by traders and investors to analyze markets, share\r\nideas, and pl